      • distanceFilter

        public Predicate<SystemSourceSet.SystemSource> distanceFilter(Location loc,
                                                              double distance)
        Description copied from interface: SourceSet
        Return a Predicate that evaluates to true if this source is within distance of the supplied Location. This Predicate performs a quick distance calculation and is used to determine whether this source should be included in a hazard calculation.
        Parameters:
        loc - Location of interest
        distance - limit

      • section

        public GriddedSurface section(int index)
        The fault section surface corresponding to the supplied index.

        This method exists because system source sets are complex and commonly encapsulate 100K+ sources. The results of a hazard calculation and deaggregation are therefore better represented in the context of individual fault sections, rather than on a per-source basis.

        Parameters:
        index - of fault section surface to retrieve
